snippet.textDisplay: Typing this before the video is even over: I’m sure you already know this, but just in case.. considering you have a male, and you want another male, please make sure you get both of them neutered. Although cats can love each other, not all do. And cats don’t actually need anyone. Two males will likely have dominance issues and will possibly mark all over your house, cat pee is extremely hard to remove the smell of. Males will possibly fight. Neutering can help these things. FEMALES CAN also mark, rare, but they can. And if you do not fix the female you will risk babies, pyometra (deathly) and the constant yowling when they’re in heat. I’d recommend neutering Declan (if you haven’t already) and spaying if you end up with a girl. ( p.s. I work for a vet before know it alls come after me) and I know they came from shelters so hopefully your shelter has/will fix them for you. :)
